  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version:\r\n```\r\n# /home/ubuntu/geth/current/geth version\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.8.10-stable\r\nGit Commit: eae63c511ceafab14b92e274c1b18bf1700e2d3d\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.10\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/usr/local/go\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nRPC calls shouldn't take too long (not sure what would be acceptable, but 10+ seconds seems to be in the realm of unacceptable)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\neth_pendingTransactions consistenly takes over 10 seconds to complete\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nIn our case, just launch node and make the rpc call:\r\n```shell\r\n$ time curl -X POST localhost:8545 -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_pendingTransactions\",\"params\":[ ],\"id\":1}' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":[]}\r\n\r\nreal    0m11.187s\r\nuser    0m0.004s\r\nsys    0m0.000s\r\n```",
